cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with a model of programmable matter that involves simple robots moving and rearranging tiles in the plane. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents algorithms for scaling and reconfiguring tile arrangements, which involve manipulating data structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may touch on the computational complexity of the reconfiguration problems it considers. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves the use of finite automata to control the behavior of the robots in the programmable matter model. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper may touch on issues related to controlling the behavior of the robots and ensuring the connectivity of the tile arrangements.
